website_summaries.verdict: There isn’t a cat on Earth who can resist sinking their fangs into meaty chunks of real turkey breast, and since it is naturally high in vitamins, and low in fat, it’s an extra healthy treat.
pros: Great for cats on a limited-ingredient diet
cons: This may seem like a trend with dehydrated human-grade cat treats, but you’ll probably have to tear these big chunks up for your cat

customer_reviews.title: A big hit with my elderly cat!
customer_reviews.text: My eighteen year old cat is addicted to this freeze dried turkey. She would eat the entire bag in one sitting if I would let her, which I won't, and I am firmly convinced she would sell me off in a heartbeat for a lifetime supply. As a previous reviewer said, it is very dry and crumbly - but my cat licks it all up eagerly. This stuff is outrageously pricey at 5.99 for a one ounce bag (over 95 dollars a pound- what kind of nonsense is that?), But the cat is addicted, so . . . By the way she does not care at all for the cod fish - she just loves the turkey.
customer_reviews.author: S. Firtch

customer_reviews.title: A win, finally
customer_reviews.text: Finally! The first treat my kitten has ever eaten! We have tried tons if brands and types and textures, no go, ever. Til these! Only complaint I have is some pieces are super hard and he struggles with them, or won't touch them altogether.
customer_reviews.author: The Viking Ninja

customer_reviews.title: Both cats love it!
customer_reviews.text: One cat chowed it down and looked for more. The other cat took a few minutes because of the unfamiliar texture. Both would have devoured the whole bag. Didn't seem to have a problem with the large chunks at all. Messy? A little but most things are with my cats. Love the healthy recipe for my fur babies.
customer_reviews.author: Linda

customer_reviews.title: Kitty loves them!

customer_reviews.title: Don’t do it
customer_reviews.text: If I found a box of these, I would leave them there. I bought these for my kitties, when I opened the package, I knew they were not going to be into it. These smell nothing like turkey, and a lot like plastic. It’s a weird texture, irregular pieces. If I had spent $6, I’d be mad. Instead, having spent $2, I’m annoyed. Please don’t waste your money.

customer_reviews.title: Great Product, Carelessly Packed for Shipping
customer_reviews.text: I have ordered this before from Amazon because it's a healthy, high quality treat, and my cat loves it. The product itself deserves 5 stars. However, this most recent Amazon order was packed such that the freeze-dried turkey arrived as crumbs (more like turkey dust), rather than the usual bite-size chunks. If this happens again with future orders, I will purchase elsewhere.

customer_reviews.title: Hard and dry, crumbles and powders when I tried to cut or break into pieces
customer_reviews.text: My cat likes the treats, but they are in big 3-4" pieces. Maybe for a larger dog where you only break it in half it might be okay, but for the price there was a lot of waste for me trying break up. I guess you could soak them in water to rehydrate them, but it's kind of expensive for just giving regular turkey. This was true for both the chicken and turkey, I'll be opening up the beef soon and will review that one.
